{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πλέκ-ω</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.86, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> πλέξω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 5.146 (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἔπλεξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.176, etc.: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> πέπλοχα (<i>Attic dialect</i> <i>accusative</i> to Hdn.Gr.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2.356), (δια-) 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ὀστέων φύσιος” 16, (ἐμ-) [prev. passage], but ἐμ-πέπλεχε [prev. work] 17 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <i>future</i> πλέξομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Perictione Philosophus cited in 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 4.28.19\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐπλεξάμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.168, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 790:\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> πλεχθήσομαι (ἐμ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1079 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; πλᾰκήσομαι (ἐπι-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 6.873\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐπλέχθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 259 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 283a, (περι-) 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 23.33 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; but also <i>aorist 2</i> ἐπλάκην [ᾰ], <i>participle</i> πλᾰκείς (ἐμ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 1236, (συμ-) 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 618 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also <i>participle</i> κατα-πλεκείς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus, variant in 2nd c.B