παντοίας παλάμας 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 644 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, μηχανὴ πεπλεγμένη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 995. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of Poets, π. ὕμνον, ῥήματα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.86, “N.” 4.94; ᾠδάς 5th c.BC: Critias Philosophus, Tragicus, Elegiacus “fragment” 1 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator; π. λόγους 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Rhesus” 834, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Hp.Mi.” 369b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>form the plot</b> of a tragedy, opposed to λύειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Poetica” 1456a9:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —hence in <i>passive</i>, μῦθοι πεπλεγμένοι <b>complex,</b> opposed to ἁπλοῖ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 1452a12, compare b32, 1459b9; συλλογισμὸς πεπλ. 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 1.29.34; πέπλεκται [ἡ τῶν συμπάντων τῶν ὄντων νομοθεσία] ἐκ.. λόγων τε καὶ αἰτίων κτλ. 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 4.3.15. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> χρόνον τοῦ ζῆν π., ={διαπλέκω}[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11, 3rd c.BC: Euphro Comicus 5. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>compound,</b> ἐκ λευκοῦ καὶ μέλανος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 12.165 (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, of words or syllables, <b>to be compounded,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 202b, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 5.30. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, <b>twine oneself round,</b> περὶ βρέτει πλεχθεὶς θεᾶς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 259 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be involved, entangled,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Vettius Valens Astrologus 169.32 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]. (Cf. Latin <i>plecto, im-plico,</i> OHG. <b>flehtan.</b>)","strongNumber":"G4120","accentedUnicode":"πλέκω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1707","matchingForm":"ἐμπλέκω","stepTransliteration":"emplekō","gloss":"to entangle/involve","_zh_tw_Gloss":"受纏繞, 纏身","_es_Gloss":"enredarse/involucrarse ","_zh_Gloss":"受缠绕, 缠身"},{"strongNumber":"G4117","matchingForm":"πλέγμα","stepTransliteration":"plegma","gloss":"braided","_zh_tw_Gloss":"編髮","_es_Gloss":"con trenzas","_zh_Gloss":"编发"}],"shortDef":"to twist together, weave, braid","mediumDef":"to twist together, weave, braid <br /><b>to interweave, weave, braid, plait, twist together</b> <ref='Mat.27.29'>Mt. 27:29</ref>; <ref='Mrk.15.17'>Mk. 15:17</ref>; <ref='Jhn.19.2'>Jn. 19:2</ref>*","stepGloss":"to weave","stepTransliteration":"plekō","count":3,"_es_Definition":"entrelazar, trenzar, entretejer","_zh_tw_Definition":"編, 編織","_zh_Definition":"编, 编织","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"tết; bện.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"編作","_es_Gloss":"tejer","_zh_Gloss":"编作"}]}